    "Description": "DOMPurify 3.1.3 through 3.3.1 and 2.5.3 through 2.5.8, fixed in 2.5.9 and 3.3.2, contain a cross-site scripting vulnerability that allows attackers to bypass attribute sanitization by exploiting five missing rawtext elements (noscript, xmp, noembed, noframes, iframe) in the `SAFE_FOR_XML` regex. Attackers can include payloads like `\u003c/noscript\u003e\u003cimg src=x onerror=alert(1)\u003e` in attribute values to execute JavaScript when sanitized output is placed inside these unprotected rawtext contexts.",
